author = Niket Nilay
description = Extending Splunk's built-in table with CSS, JS and SplunkJS
version = 1.0.0

______________________
Dependencies:
______________________
Requires Splunk Dashboard Examples App for linking to Table examples and Dark Theme workaround: https://splunkbase.splunk.com/app/1603/
Requires Status Indicator - Custom Visualization for Icons in Examples: https://splunkbase.splunk.com/app/3119/

______________________
Examples:
______________________
1. Reference to Splunk Dashboard Examples App's Table Examples using Built In, Simple XML, Simple XML CSS and JS extensions with Splunk JS Stack.
2. Reference to Splunk Style Guide for Tables in Splunk UI.
3. Splunk Table Sparkline Examples including jQury Sparkline through Simple XML JS extension for creating Composite Sparkline (custom x-axis not required to be time).
4. Apply custom style to Splunk Table using Simple XML CSS extension.
5. SplunkJS overview for TableView with example of highlighting selected text in multiple tables.
6. Adding HTML input to Splunk table using Simple XML CSS/JS extension and SplunkJS stack.
7. Adding Context Menu to Splunk tables using Modal Pop-Up. Using jQuery.UI draggable() event to allow dragging of modal pop-up.
8. Example with creation of Data Bars within table. Create stacked bar chart within table or Create Funnel Chart/Pyramid Chart with Table.
9. Show table as tile. Similar to Status Indicator. Option to switch between compressed box view with Tooltip or else regular tile with Icon and details. Allows drilldown.
10. Create slider using table with CSS extension and auto-rotate between KPIs based on Slider interval using JS Extension.
11. Create html table using search result with html content. Example also demos similar tile creation using built in Splunk Table.

______________________
Known Issue:
______________________
Table rendering randomly does not seem to work for Title Tables with Font awesome.